Manchester City Women are set to continue their summer overhaul by signing Barcelona’s Leila Ouahabi and Atletico Madrid’s Laia Aleixandri on free transfers, The Athletic can reveal. Ouahabi, who lost her starting spot at left-back to Fridolina Rolfo in the 2021-22 season, leaves Barcelona after 13 years, while central defender Aleixandri is also out of contract and has opted for a move to Manchester. City have already secured the services of Atletico striker Deyna Castellano on a three-year deal. -Advertisement- Manager Gareth Taylor is overseeing a significant rebuild with a string of players leaving the club. Georgia Stanway has completed a move to Bayern Munich, while fellow England international Lucy Bronze, Scotland midfielder Caroline Weir and France goalkeeper Karima Benameur Taieb will all leave when their contracts expire this month. Taylor’s side recovered from an injury-hampered poor start to finish third in the Women’s Super League table and qualify for the 2022-23 Champions League.